name: Hydraulic Press
description:
Hydraulic press works due to "Pascal's Law".
In this level you have a pipe with 2 endings - smaller and bigger.
Both of the endings have a moveable lid placed on top of them.
Due to Pascal's law applying small force on the smaller lid will result in a larger force on the bigger lid.
The force scales proportionaly to the ratio of the areas - roughly 2.5 in this case.
Try dragging and putting down the prepared red (~10Kg) and green (~25Kg) objects onto the lids.
Hint: Start with the green one onto the bigger lid.
